General  Information
Test case description	Norman/UI Composer
Test case ID		Version	V1
CSN Component	  
Estimated time for manual test execution	30 min
Risk Level (1-5)	1
Automation readiness	
Reviewed by	Norman/UI Composer
Description
Purpose/ goal of the test case	
Verify that an user be able to view UI Library Mash Up in UI Composer

Business scenario/User Story
	  

The user shall be able to use all UI libraries that are set up available in the tenant. The user shall be able to pick up UI elements from these libraries, mix them up and place them on the canvas.
The initial libraries are of UI5 and Angular for Jan.
 
Acceptance Criteria
•	The user shall be able to see all UI libraries that are set up in the tenant.
•	The library list is selectable.
•	While working on the canvas, the user shall be able to drag a UI element from a selected UI library and drop it on the canvas.
•	While working on the canvas the user shall be able to drag a UI element from another selected UI library and drop it on the canvas in the mix of UI elements from different UI libraries.
  
Preparations
Setup/Configuration steps (if necessary)
An user had signed up to Project Norman with the name, email address and password

User Logon Information/ Roles

Navigation path to reach the application (i.e. URL)


Test Scenarios 
                  

Verify an user be able to view the list of UI libraries

	

Verify anuser be able to select each UI Catalog from the Library list

	

Verify an user be able to view the list of UI elements of each UI library   

	

Verify an user be able to drag and drop an element from UI Element list for each libraries onto the page   

	


Variant (eg. Mac,  Windows,  browser compatibility)

Execute the test with  Desktop Windows /Chrome and Mac/Safari and Chrome  

